You can see up the top here that behaves how it's supposed to.

02:24.710 --> 02:28.250
So as you can see there's very nice controls here for constraints.

02:28.250 --> 02:33.200
And then we have a layer section and this is where we can get some overlay settings if we want something

02:33.200 --> 02:34.320
to multiply.

02:34.610 --> 02:41.310
So why it multiplied by anything is that color changes to red you can kind of see how it's transparent.

02:41.360 --> 02:44.800
I'm going to hold out command here and zoom in so you can kind of see what that's doing.

02:44.990 --> 02:50.110
But you can play with some different overlay effects here and get a nice style that you want.

02:50.120 --> 02:54.140
I'm just going to change this back to white and just normal is fine.

02:54.440 --> 03:00.560
So you have some nice opacity effects here you can increase the transparency here or just simply hide

03:00.560 --> 03:02.070
the layer if you want to.

03:02.420 --> 03:07.250
And then you have full control so this is where you'll change the actual color and we saw that as I

03:07.250 --> 03:13.310
was changing this around so you can change this to blue and we can create a feel on top of a feel which

03:13.310 --> 03:14.390
is really great.

03:14.420 --> 03:21.860
So if I click on the plus icon here you can see that I have a linear feel on top of a solid feel so

03:21.860 --> 03:28.960
that gives us this nice white on top of blue and I can change the angle of these pretty quickly.

03:30.340 --> 03:34.590
And just get a nice effect if I want something like that looks good.

03:35.870 --> 03:38.390
And so multiple fill options.

03:38.600 --> 03:47.000
And within this fill color you can fill with the solid color a linear color radial angular diamond or

03:47.000 --> 03:48.290
an actual image.

03:48.290 --> 03:52.400
So if you click on image here that's going to ask you to choose an image and you can find one in your

03:52.400 --> 03:55.000
file and fill that image.

03:55.040 --> 04:01.160
If I ever want to delete a feel I can just click on the file here and just click this subtract button

04:01.190 --> 04:02.530
and then I'll remove that.

04:02.720 --> 04:04.710
And now I'll turn this back to white.

04:05.980 --> 04:07.430
And we have stroke.

04:07.720 --> 04:10.280
